Class Internship

java.lang.Object
Internship
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Internship extends Object implements Serializable
Represents an internship opportunity offered by a company. Stores details such as title, description, application dates, preferred major, number of slots, and visibility status.

      Creates a new internship with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      title - the internship title
      description - a description of the internship
      level - the internship level
      preferredMajor - the preferred student major
      appOpenDate - the application opening date
      appCloseDate - the application closing date
      status - the current internship status
      companyName - the name of the company offering the internship
      companyRep - the company representative responsible
      numSlots - the total number of available slots
      visibility - whether the internship is visible to students
